[4.369187, "o", "\u001b[?2004h>   \r\n\u001b[?2004l\r\u001b[?2004h> "]
[4.369906, "o", "  - Sadly due to async I/O buffering and multi-process scheduling, the events within each log file are out of order, and in some events the LLM calls failed due to various reasons.\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r"]
[4.369978, "o", "\u001b[?2004h> \r\n\u001b[?2004l\r"]
[4.370044, "o", "\u001b[?2004h> - Goal\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r\u001b[?2004h"]
[4.370101, "o", "> "]
[4.370401, "o", "  - Your task is to save the per-run logs for both role, and compute the per-run accuracy.\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r"]
[4.370431, "o", "\u001b[?2004h> "]
[4.370488, "o", "  - Step 1\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r\u001b[?2004h> "]
[4.371046, "o", "    - Sort the two given log files according to the timestamp, then save 3 per-run generator log files and 3 per-run judge log files:\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r"]
[4.371139, "o", "\u001b[?2004h> "]
[4.371474, "o", "      - For generator: for each question_id, sort that question_id'\"'\"'s records by timestamp ascending.\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r"]
[4.371535, "o", "\u001b[?2004h> "]
[4.371957, "o", "      - Assign the earliest to - run_1_generator.jsonl, the middle to run_2_generator.jsonl, the latest run_3_generator.jsonl.\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r"]
[4.371973, "o", "\u001b[?2004h"]
[4.372028, "o", "> "]
[4.372289, "o", "      - For judge: assign the corresponding events to run_1_judge.jsonl, run_2_judge.jsonl, run_3_judge.jsonl\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r"]
[4.372302, "o", "\u001b[?2004h> "]
[4.372692, "o", "    - After the assignment, each run_X_{role}.jsonl must contain exactly 10 lines (one per question_id) and be sorted by timestamp ascending.\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r"]
[4.372825, "o", "\u001b[?2004h> "]
[4.373344, "o", "    - Some records will have API call errors. A record is an error if the '\"'\"'prediction'\"'\"' or '\"'\"'target'\"'\"' fields contain (case-insensitive) any of: '\"'\"'Quota Exceeds'\"'\"', '\"'\"'API Error'\"'\"', '\"'\"'Timeout'\"'\"'.\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r"]
[4.373407, "o", "\u001b[?2004h> "]
[4.373638, "o", "    - Error records must still appear in the corresponding run_X_{role}.jsonl.\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r"]
[4.373693, "o", "\u001b[?2004h> "]
[4.374091, "o", "    - Note: no events have identical timestamps, and there will be exactly three events exist for the same question_id and role in the given input files.\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r"]
[4.374133, "o", "\u001b[?2004h> \r\n\u001b[?2004l\r"]
[4.374168, "o", "\u001b[?2004h"]
[4.374203, "o", "> "]
[4.374492, "o", "  - Step 2: compute accuracy for each run after excluding error records and unmatched pairs and save to results.json\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r"]
[4.374508, "o", "\u001b[?2004h> "]
[4.374905, "o", "    - Within each run_index r, for every question_id, compare the exact match of generator'\"'\"'s prediction and judge'\"'\"'s target as integers.\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r"]
[4.374945, "o", "\u001b[?2004h"]
[4.375028, "o", "> "]
[4.375283, "o", "    - Exclude from evaluation any [prediction, target] pair where either side is an error event (contains any of the error marker).\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r"]
[4.375357, "o", "\u001b[?2004h"]
[4.375449, "o", "> "]
[4.375662, "o", "    - The final accuracy = correct / total computed in double precision; round half up to two decimals (e.g., 0.675 → 0.68).\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r"]
[4.375769, "o", "\u001b[?2004h> "]
[4.37589, "o", "    - If total = 0 for a run, set \"accuracy\": null (JSON null).\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r"]
[4.375944, "o", "\u001b[?2004h> \r\n\u001b[?2004l\r\u001b[?2004h> "]
[4.376038, "o", "- Inputs (exactly these 2 files)\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r"]
[4.376095, "o", "\u001b[?2004h> "]
[4.376299, "o", "  - Two files: /app/raw_logs/generator.log and /app/raw_logs/judge.log (30 events each).\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r"]
[4.376357, "o", "\u001b[?2004h> "]
[4.376596, "o", "    - Some LLM calls error out due to server-side constraints (quota, transient API failures, timeouts).\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r"]
[4.376681, "o", "\u001b[?2004h> "]
[4.376728, "o", "    - Generator record fields:\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r"]
[4.376768, "o", "\u001b[?2004h> "]
[4.376997, "o", "      - timestamp (ISO-8601 UTC with microseconds, e.g., 2025-08-20T04:01:31.123456Z)\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r"]
[4.377069, "o", "\u001b[?2004h> "]
[4.377109, "o", "      - question_id (string)\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r"]
[4.37715, "o", "\u001b[?2004h> "]
[4.377328, "o", "      - prediction (string: either an integer literal in [0,1000] or an error marker)\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r"]
[4.377427, "o", "\u001b[?2004h> "]
[4.377468, "o", "    - Judge record fields:\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r\u001b[?2004h"]
[4.377513, "o", "> "]
[4.377561, "o", "      - timestamp (same format)\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r"]
[4.377611, "o", "\u001b[?2004h> "]
[4.377693, "o", "      - question_id (string)\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r\u001b[?2004h> "]
[4.377917, "o", "      - target (string: either an integer literal in [0,1000] or an error marker)\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r"]
[4.37797, "o", "\u001b[?2004h> "]
[4.378269, "o", "    - Error markers (case-insensitive substring match): '\"'\"'Quota Exceeds'\"'\"', '\"'\"'API Error'\"'\"', '\"'\"'Timeout'\"'\"'.\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r"]
[4.378325, "o", "\u001b[?2004h> \r\n\u001b[?2004l\r"]
[4.378364, "o", "\u001b[?2004h> "]
[4.378435, "o", "- Outputs (exactly these seven files)\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r\u001b[?2004h> "]
[4.378582, "o", "  - /app/recovered_logs/run_1_generator.jsonl\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r"]
[4.378645, "o", "\u001b[?2004h> "]
[4.37871, "o", "  - /app/recovered_logs/run_1_judge.jsonl\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r"]
[4.378755, "o", "\u001b[?2004h> "]
[4.378893, "o", "  - /app/recovered_logs/run_2_generator.jsonl\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r\u001b[?2004h> "]
[4.379008, "o", "  - /app/recovered_logs/run_2_judge.jsonl\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r"]
[4.379039, "o", "\u001b[?2004h> "]
[4.379178, "o", "  - /app/recovered_logs/run_3_generator.jsonl\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r\u001b[?2004h> "]
[4.379313, "o", "  - /app/recovered_logs/run_3_judge.jsonl\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r"]
[4.379369, "o", "\u001b[?2004h"]
[4.379415, "o", "> "]
[4.379464, "o", "  - /app/recovered_logs/results.json\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r"]
[4.379527, "o", "\u001b[?2004h> \r\n\u001b[?2004l\r\u001b[?2004h> "]
[4.379597, "o", "Output Schema:\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r\u001b[?2004h"]
[4.37964, "o", "> \r\n\u001b[?2004l\r\u001b[?2004h> "]
[4.379716, "o", "  - Formatting requirements (strict):\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r"]
[4.379795, "o", "\u001b[?2004h> "]
[4.380149, "o", "    - For all `run_{run_id}_*.jsonl` files, serialize JSON in compact form with no extra whitespace (no spaces after `:` or `,`).\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r"]
[4.380203, "o", "\u001b[?2004h> "]
[4.380474, "o", "    - Keep object key order exactly as shown in the examples: `timestamp`, `question_id`, then `prediction` (generator) or `target` (judge).\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r"]
[4.380517, "o", "\u001b[?2004h> "]
[4.380652, "o", "    - Each line must be exactly one JSON object terminated by a single `\\n` newline.\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r\u001b[?2004h> "]
[4.3809, "o", "    - Each `run_{run_id}_*.jsonl` must contain exactly 10 lines and be sorted by `timestamp` ascending (include error records).\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r"]
[4.380959, "o", "\u001b[?2004h> "]
[4.381112, "o", "    - Example (Python): `json.dumps(obj, separators=('\"'\"','\"'\"', '\"'\"':'\"'\"'))`.\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r\u001b[?2004h> \r\n\u001b[?2004l\r"]
[4.381151, "o", "\u001b[?2004h> "]
[4.381285, "o", "  - Schema for generator: run_{run_id}_generator.jsonl (10 lines, one JSON object per event)\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r"]
[4.381325, "o", "\u001b[?2004h> "]
[4.381381, "o", "    - Normal example:\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r"]
[4.381472, "o", "\u001b[?2004h>       ```json\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r"]
[4.381522, "o", "\u001b[?2004h> "]
[4.381604, "o", "      {\"timestamp\":\"2025-08-20T04:01:31.123456Z\",\"question_id\":\"q-0007\",\"prediction\":\"142\"}\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r"]
[4.381645, "o", "\u001b[?2004h> "]
[4.381684, "o", "      ```\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r\u001b[?2004h> \r\n\u001b[?2004l\r"]
[4.381718, "o", "\u001b[?2004h> "]
[4.381797, "o", "    - Error LLM call example:\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r\u001b[?2004h> "]
[4.3819, "o", "      ```json\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r\u001b[?2004h> "]
[4.38207, "o", "      {\"timestamp\":\"2025-09-12T03:01:21.123456Z\",\"question_id\":\"q-0005\",\"prediction\":\"Timeout\"}\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r"]
[4.38214, "o", "\u001b[?2004h>       ```\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r\u001b[?2004h"]
[4.382213, "o", "> \r\n\u001b[?2004l\r"]
[4.382277, "o", "\u001b[?2004h> "]
[4.382396, "o", "  - Schema for judge: run_{run_id}_judge.jsonl (10 lines, one JSON object per event)\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r"]
[4.382445, "o", "\u001b[?2004h> \r\n\u001b[?2004l\r\u001b[?2004h> "]
[4.382521, "o", "    - Normal example:\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r"]
[4.382563, "o", "\u001b[?2004h>     ```json\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r"]
[4.382616, "o", "\u001b[?2004h> "]
[4.38281, "o", "    {\"timestamp\":\"2025-08-20T04:01:31.123456Z\",\"question_id\":\"q-0007\",\"target\":\"123\"}\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r"]
[4.382864, "o", "\u001b[?2004h>     ```\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r"]
[4.382904, "o", "\u001b[?2004h> \r\n\u001b[?2004l\r\u001b[?2004h"]
[4.382969, "o", "> "]
[4.383024, "o", "    - Error LLM call example:\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r"]
[4.383069, "o", "\u001b[?2004h> \r\n\u001b[?2004l\r\u001b[?2004h> "]
[4.383111, "o", "    ```json\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r\u001b[?2004h"]
[4.383126, "o", "> "]
[4.383324, "o", "    {\"timestamp\":\"2025-09-12T03:01:21.123456Z\",\"question_id\":\"q-0005\",\"target\":\"API Error\"}\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r"]
[4.383343, "o", "\u001b[?2004h> "]
[4.38341, "o", "    ```\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r\u001b[?2004h> "]
[4.383487, "o", "  - Schema for results.json:\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r"]
[4.383532, "o", "\u001b[?2004h>     ```json\r\n"]
[4.383572, "o", "\u001b[?2004l\r"]
[4.383652, "o", "\u001b[?2004h>     {\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r\u001b[?2004h>       \"runs\": [\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r"]
[4.383718, "o", "\u001b[?2004h> "]
[4.383876, "o", "        { \"run_index\": 1, \"correct\": 9, \"total\": 10, \"accuracy\": 0.90 },\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r"]
[4.383934, "o", "\u001b[?2004h> "]
[4.384093, "o", "        { \"run_index\": 2, \"correct\": 6, \"total\":  6, \"accuracy\": 1.00 },\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r\u001b[?2004h"]
[4.384107, "o", "> "]
[4.384266, "o", "        { \"run_index\": 3, \"correct\": 3, \"total\":  9, \"accuracy\": 0.33 }\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r"]
[4.384323, "o", "\u001b[?2004h> "]
[4.384386, "o", "      ]\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r\u001b[?2004h>     }\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r\u001b[?2004h> "]
[4.384446, "o", "    ```'; tmux wait -S done\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r"]
[7.336668, "o", "\u001b[32mDownloading\u001b[39m https://github.com/denodrivers/sqlite3/releases/download/0.12.0/libsqlite3.so\r\n"]
[19.978474, "o", "[TodoWrite]\r\n"]
[78.299708, "o", "[Read]\r\n[Read]\r\n"]
[129.279225, "o", "[Write]\r\n"]
[193.485641, "o", "[TodoWrite]\r\n"]
[212.560984, "o", "[Bash]\r\n"]
[212.667367, "o", "\u001b[36m⠙\u001b[39m \u001b[33m[Bash: Run the log processing script]\u001b[39m \u001b[2m(0:29 remaining)\u001b[22m\r\n"]
[212.667702, "o", "\u001b[2m(esc interrupt | ctrl+o expand)\u001b[22m\r\n"]
